content.text:
Context is clear now: this webUI work is meant to be a thin Codex workbench over the live Offdex bridge, not a separate browser-native product. The current diff is aligned with that. It expands the browser from simple chat into a real bridge-backed workbench with thread timelines, live diffs, approvals, archived threads, runtime/config controls, plugin/skill/app inventory, and remote file browse/search/attach.

I pushed the durable-memory docs separately on `docs/durable-memory` at `618d026`. PR link: [docs/durable-memory](https://github.com/Dhruv2mars/offdex/pull/new/docs/durable-memory). I also committed and pushed the workbench branch on `feat/webui-production-workbench` at `5add3f8`. PR link: [feat/webui-production-workbench](https://github.com/Dhruv2mars/offdex/pull/new/feat/webui-production-workbench).

Verification is solid: targeted tests passed, `bun run typecheck` passed, and a live bridge smoke check against `/health`, `/snapshot`, `/inventory`, `/files`, and `/file-search` succeeded on a real authenticated Codex bridge. The one gap is browser-tooling: `agent-browser` connected but didn’t return snapshot/eval output reliably in this shell, so I used live endpoint smoke instead of a full visual pass.

Next move is straightforward: open the workbench PR, then do one manual browser pass on `/webui` before merge focused on the actual interactive flows this feature adds: connect, start thread, attach/search files, diff panel, permissions rail, archive/unarchive, and runtime/config toggles. `docs/` is still untracked in this worktree by design, so it won’t pollute the workbench branch unless you want it cleaned up locally.

