`main` is pushed at `c8f0a95`, and local plus `origin/main` are clean and identical.

This batch moved the webUI forward in two real parity areas. First, the bridge/protocol/web timeline now treats common runtime activity as first-class UI instead of dumping it into `unknown`: task lifecycle, tool/search/file activity, and token usage now render as dedicated workbench rows. Second, the diff panel is no longer just a raw blob; it now parses unified diffs into file-aware review cards with per-file counts and a review summary. The main code is in [web-app-client.tsx](/Users/dhruv2mars/dev/github/offdex/apps/web/app/(app)/webui/web-app-client.tsx:1), [codex-app-server.ts](/Users/dhruv2mars/dev/github/offdex/packages/bridge/src/codex-app-server.ts:1), and [index.ts](/Users/dhruv2mars/dev/github/offdex/packages/protocol/src/index.ts:1), with coverage added in [webui-diff.test.ts](/Users/dhruv2mars/dev/github/offdex/apps/web/test/webui-diff.test.ts:1) and [codex-app-server.test.ts](/Users/dhruv2mars/dev/github/offdex/packages/bridge/test/codex-app-server.test.ts:1).

Verification passed:
- `bun run typecheck`
- `bun test apps/web/test/design-system.test.ts apps/web/test/webui-diff.test.ts packages/bridge/test/codex-app-server.test.ts packages/protocol/test/index.test.ts apps/mobile/test/bridge-workspace-controller.test.ts`
- live `/webui` load verified with `agent-browser` on `http://localhost:3010/webui`

It would still be dishonest to call this desktop parity. The biggest remaining gaps are connected review workflows end to end, richer tool/result fidelity in active sessions, and deeper settings/workspace/remote behaviors. The next slice should be the connected review loop: review thread start, findings display, diff acceptance/rejection affordances, and thread recovery around that flow.

